{
  "stem": "19807.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a list of-- of children that-- and they start sending those children group by group.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was slated in a group of 42, which it came just shortly before the-- the Nazis had left.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was slated to leave during the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everybody was able to leave during the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now remember, those were not smuggled.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Those were given official passports, papers, British visas.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we are put on a train by ourselves, 42 children, after we have achieved all this status, to get the papers, to be registered, to-- to-- to have all the documentation approved that we didn't own money, all this.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we're put on a train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the last thing I remember-- after we made all these preparations very anxiously and my father and the whole family was very, very anxious for-- for me to do that-- unfortunately, I couldn't take my kid brother with me.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was a-- but many of our friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we were a group of 42 children that we went from-- from Bulgaria, on the train.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the last thing I remember, my mother running alongside the train-- waving goodbye.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I would say this, that we were lucky, because five years later, the entire family came to Israel.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Like I said, like close to 46,000, 44,000 Jews were allowed to leave Bulgaria willingly.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were not expelled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were not forced.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that was one thing I don't know the mechanics how it was done, but the Communists allowed them to leave.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And now the ones that remained there were people who wanted to stay there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was-- it was very difficult to leave the family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the most difficult thing for me was to leave my kid brother.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
